Right.

The only other important criteria that come to mind are:
    5) it doesn't cause significant conflicts.

In other words, if J. Random Package happens to contain a file named, say,
"plain.tex", we aren't going to install it :).  We try to work with the
author to resolve conflicts.  Conflicts can happen in other ways too,
but are surprisingly rare.

Much more common is:
    6) we notice it.

In other words, I'm sure there are many things on CTAN which meet 1-4
and are not in TL simply because Sebastian did not notice them to
incorporate them.  Post-Sebastian, we have never even managed to look at
everything *in TL*, let alone everything on CTAN.  

So if there are things on CTAN which meet 1-5 and aren't in TL, report
it here.  

    http://tug.ctan.org/tex-archive/macros/plain/contrib/timetable/timetable.tex

